STUYVESANT, Respondent, v. NEW YORK FLOATING DRY-DOCK CO., Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. February 16, 1894.) Action by Amelia Stuyvesant against the New York Floating Dry-Dock Company.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. X, and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JX

J. Adriance Bush, for appellant. Geo. V. N. Baldwin, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs on opinion of referee.
